Inkjet
	Sprays tiny dots of ink on paper [[img http://www.techfresh.net/wp-content/uploads/2006/10/dell_photo-all-in-one-926-inkjet-printer.jpg]]
	Prints in color
		Ink is stored in cartriges contained in the printhead, which moves back and forth across the page
		Colors (CMYK)
			Cyan, Magneta, Yellow, Black
	Print quality features
		Print Resolution - density of ink (dpi)
		Print speed (pages per minute)
	Cheap to buy, expensive to operate
------------------------------------------
Dye Sublimation
	Uses heat to change solid ink to vapor and place on paper [[img http://www.togblog.biz/wp-content/uploads/2010/05/DyeSubDiagram-copy1-copy.jpg]]
	Uses roll of heat sensitive plastic film embeded with page sized sections of each color
	Prints very high-quality color documents or photos
	Requires one pass for each color
	Generally, slow and expensive to operate
------------------------------------------
Solid Ink
	Prints color
	Utilizes solid sticks of ink
	Prints in one pass
	Very expensive
